<subSubSection box="[1717,2105,2365,2407]" pageId="212" pageNumber="817" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="212.[1377,2105,2365,2487]" box="[1717,2105,2365,2407]" pageId="212" pageNumber="817">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="W. W. A. Phillips" baseAuthorityYear="1929" box="[1717,2105,2365,2407]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Srilankamys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="212" pageNumber="817" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ohiensiis">Srilankamys ohiensiis</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="212" pageNumber="817" type="vernacular_names">
<paragraph blockId="212.[1377,2105,2365,2487]" box="[1378,2073,2426,2447]" pageId="212" pageNumber="817">French: Rat d'Ohiya / German: Ohiya-Ratte / Spanish: Rata de Ohiya</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="212.[1377,2105,2365,2487]" lastBlockId="212.[1985,2583,2531,2958]" pageId="212" pageNumber="817">
Other common names: Phillips's Srilankamys 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1989,2142,2531,2565]" pageId="212" pageNumber="817">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="W. W. A. Phillips, 1929" authorityName="W. W. A. Phillips" authorityYear="1929" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Rattus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="212" pageNumber="817" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ohiensis">Rattus ohiensis W. W. A. Phillips, 1929</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation box="[2071,2525,2570,2604]" pageId="212" pageNumber="817">West Haputale, Ohiya, Sri Lanka.</materialsCitation>
G. G. Musser in 1981 highlighted morphological differences among S. ohienss, 
<taxonomicName box="[1991,2075,2696,2721]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Rattus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="212" pageNumber="817" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rattus</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName box="[2158,2291,2696,2721]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Niviventer" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="212" pageNumber="817" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Niviventer</taxonomicName>
. A recent molecular study confirmed position of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Musser" authorityYear="1981" box="[2428,2583,2728,2762]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Srilankamys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="212" pageNumber="817" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Srilankamys</taxonomicName>
within the 
<taxonomicName box="[2155,2250,2767,2801]" pageId="212" pageNumber="883" rank="tribe" tribe="Rattini">Rattini</taxonomicName>
, and E. V. Buzan and colleagues in 2011 and S.J. Steppan and J. J. Schenk in 2017 identified it as the basal taxon of the 
<taxonomicName box="[2171,2263,2889,2918]" pageId="212" pageNumber="883" rank="tribe" tribe="Rattini">Rattini</taxonomicName>
division. Monotypic. 
<subSubSection box="[1990,2348,2916,2958]" pageId="212" pageNumber="817" type="distribution">
<caption box="[1990,2348,2916,2958]" inLine="true" pageId="212" pageNumber="817" startId="212.[1990,2162,2916,2958]" targetBox="[1375,1967,2543,2958]" targetPageId="212">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1990,2166,2916,2958]" pageId="212" pageNumber="817">Distribution.</emphasis>
C Sri Lanka.
</caption>
</subSubSection>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="213" lastPageNumber="818" pageId="212" pageNumber="817" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="212.[1378,2581,2964,3077]" pageId="212" pageNumber="817">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1378,1627,2964,2998]" pageId="212" pageNumber="817">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head—body 145 mm,tail 173 mm, hindfoot 31 mm, ear 20 mm. No specific data are available for body weight. The Ohia Rat is medium-sized, with brown dorsum and pale cream venter, sharply demarcated from dorsum. Fur is soft, fine,
